    "More recently, 26 publications published in the WoS database between 2011 and 2019 were used by Navarrete-Oyarce et al. (2021), while Lopes and Penela (2021) combined data from WoS and Scopus.",
    "Likewise, Di Vaio et al. (2020) used 60 English-language publications from 1990 to 2019 to achieve the respective objective.",
    "Kirchherr et al. (2017) thoroughly reviewed 114 circular economy definitions (CE) definitions, demonstrating the wide range of interpretations and applications of CE principles.",
    "Their research highlighted that while the fundamental concept of reducing, reusing, and recycling resources is widely accepted, the practical implementation of CE varies significantly across different industries and regions.",
    "This variation indicates the necessity for customised strategies that consider local economic, environmental, and social conditions to apply CE practices effectively."
